---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar";
import Contact from "../components/Contact";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | SynVoke">
    <Navbar client:load />

    <main
        class="pt-32 pb-24 min-h-[80vh] bg-white text-gray-900 border-b border-gray-100"
    >
        <div class="container mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 max-w-4xl pt-16">
            <h1
                class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-display font-bold mb-6 text-gray-900"
            >
                Privacy Policy
            </h1>
            <p
                class="text-gray-500 font-mono text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-16"
            >
                Last Updated: March 2026
            </p>

            <div class="prose prose-lg prose-indigo max-w-none text-gray-600">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    1. Information We Collect
                </h2>
                <p>
                    When you contact SynVoke, we may collect business contact
                    information including your name, email address, phone
                    number, and any details regarding your engineering needs
                    that you provide to us through our contact forms or emails.
                    The Admin Portal uses essential analytics for internal
                    monitoring, but does not deploy mass tracking pixels.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    2. How We Use Your Information
                </h2>
                <p>
                    The information you provide is strictly used to communicate
                    with you regarding your project requirements, official
                    quotations, job applications, billing, and providing the
                    agreed-upon engineering services. We do not sell your
                    personal data to third parties.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    3. Data Security and Storage
                </h2>
                <p>
                    We value the trust you place in us to build secure systems.
                    We implement industry-standard security measures, physical
                    protections, and backend encryption methodologies to protect
                    the data you share with us against unauthorized access or
                    alteration.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    4. Cookies and Technologies
                </h2>
                <p>
                    SynVoke uses limited browser storage (like localStorage)
                    strictly to ensure functional performance, including
                    remembering UI selections to provide seamless navigation,
                    especially within internal portals. We do not use cross-site
                    tracking cookies.
                </p>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-4">
                    5. Contact Us regarding Privacy
                </h2>
                <p>
                    If you have questions about how we handle data, or if you
                    need us to remove specific contact records, you can reach
                    out to our privacy compliance team via email at <strong
                        >contact.synvoke@gmail.com</strong
                    >.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <Contact client:visible />
</Layout>
